gomodel:SYNGO_1304  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Knockdown of Homer3 activates mGluR1 signaling in cerebellar neurons suggesting that Homer3 is a negative regulator of mGluR signaling.\n\n43/11/2017 Pim\n- The authors show that interaction of Homer3 with the receptor modulates the intrinsic activity of the mGluRs: \"Our data show that neuronal activity-dependent modulation of the interaction between a GPCR and its associated intracellular protein can elicit receptor activity independently of agonist binding, and with a time constant different from that of agonist-mediated activation.\". Experimental description: from M&M: \"Cerebellar cultures were prepared from one-week-old mice\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6153-3586" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2666-0758" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-03" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1304" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

